## Bead
`etude-roadmap.3` â€” Retro nudge: opt-in reminder when retro is overdue.

## Goal
Add an opt-in "retro nudge" line emitted to **stderr** by any `etude` command
when, per workflow.yaml, the number of captured runs since the most recent
retro reaches a configured threshold. Provide a `dismiss` subcommand to
snooze and a `status` subcommand to introspect.

## Acceptance criteria (verbatim from bead)
1. Off by default; byte-identical behavior for repos with no nudge config.
2. Opt-in via `retros.nudge { enabled, threshold }` in `.etude/workflow.yaml`;
   threshold must be >= 1 when enabled.
3. Trigger: count of runs with `Created` strictly after the most recent
   retro's `Created` (any scope), >= threshold; with zero retros, total runs
   >= threshold.
4. Output: single line on **stderr**, after the subcommand has finished
   (success or failure), only for real subcommands (not help/version, not
   for `etude retro nudge dismiss` itself).
5. Snooze: `etude retro nudge dismiss [--for N]` (default 1) records a
   snooze in `.git/etude/retro-nudge-snooze.json`. Snooze suppresses while
   `current_runs_since_last_retro - runs_at_snooze < snooze_for`.
6. Status: `etude retro nudge status` prints a JSON object to stdout with
   `enabled, threshold, runs_since_last_retro, last_retro_id, overdue,
   snoozed_until_runs, would_emit`.
7. Tests cover config, calculator, snooze round-trip, root-stderr emission,
   dismiss and status subcommands.
8. Docs: extend `docs/retro.md` with a Nudge section.

## Architecture invariants we will respect
- `docs/` documents implemented behavior only; planning notes stay under
  `docs/plans/`. Update `docs/retro.md` after the feature works.
- One bead = one commit. No bundled work.
- `runs` and `retros` come from `refs/etude/runs/*` and `refs/etude/retros/*`
